			Company Description 


			NAHL Group Plc provides outsourced and online marketing services. The company operates through five segments: Pre-LASPO ATE, Conveyancing, Critical Care, Other segments, Personal Injury and One-off items. The Pre-LASPO ATE segment commissions received for the use of after the event insurance policie...
		


                NAHL Group Plc provides outsourced and online marketing services. The company operates through five segments: Pre-LASPO ATE, Conveyancing, Critical Care, Other segments, Personal Injury and One-off items. The Pre-LASPO ATE segment commissions received for the use of after the event insurance policies by solicitor firms. The Conveyancing segment provides online marketing services to target home buyers and sellers in England and Wales. It offers services to panel law firms and surveyors in the conveyancing sector and the provision of conveyancing searches for solicitors and licensed conveyancers. The Critical Care segment offers expert witness reports and case management support services within the medico-legal framework for multi-track cases. The Other segments manage group activities or not specifically related to a product and including share based payments. The Personal Injury segment consists of revenue from the provision of enquiries to the panel law firms, based on a cost plus margin model, plus commissions received from providers for the sale of additional products by them to the Panel Law Firms. The One-off items segment provides costs associated services with the acquisition of subsidiary undertakings, share based payments and amortization charges on intangible assets recognized as part of business combination. The company was founded in 1993 and is headquartered in Kettering, the United Kingdom.
            




