or Close  130.88 (08/02/17)     1 Day    NAH 0.76%     DJIA 0.04%     Russell 2K -0.26%     Business/Consumer Services 0.06%                             Overview Profile     Overview Profile Financials Income Statement Balance Sheet Cash Flow Research & Ratings Historical Prices Options Advanced Charting              Company Info NAHL Group PLC        1430 Montagu Court Kettering Northamptonshire NN15 6XR United Kingdom   Website Map       Employees  200    Sector  Consumer Services      Sales or Revenue  49.39 M    Industry  Business/Consumer Services      1Y Sales Change   -2.62%     Fiscal Year Ends  December 31 Download Reports                      Description NAHL Group PLC      NAHL Group Plc provides outsourced and online marketing services. The company operates through five segments: Pre-LASPO ATE, Conveyancing, Critical Care, Other segments, Personal Injury and One-off items. The Pre-LASPO ATE segment commissions received for the use of after the event insurance policies by solicitor firms. The Conveyancing segment provides online marketing services to target home buyers and sellers in England and Wales. It offers services to panel law firms and surveyors in the conveyancing sector and the provision of conveyancing searches for solicitors and licensed conveyancers. The Critical Care segment offers expert witness reports and case management support services within the medico-legal framework for multi-track cases. The Other segments manage group activities or not specifically related to a product and including share based payments. The Personal Injury segment consists of revenue from the provision of enquiries to the panel law firms, based on a cost plus margin model, plus commissions received from providers for the sale of additional products by them to the Panel Law Firms. The One-off items segment provides costs associated services with the acquisition of subsidiary undertakings, share based payments and amortization charges on intangible assets recognized as part of business combination. The company was founded in 1993 and is headquartered in Kettering, the United Kingdom.    expand             Key People NAHL Group PLC   Board of Directors    Name/Title Current Board Membership          Robert Stephen Halbert, 58  Chairman   NAHL Group Plc, Consumer Champion Group Ltd., Safestyle UK Plc      John Russell Atkinson, 51  Chief Executive Officer & Director   NAHL Group Plc      Stephen Dolton, 55  Chief Financial Officer & Director   NAHL Group Plc      Tim Aspinall,   Non-Executive Director   NAHL Group Plc      Gillian Dawn Celia Kent, 54  Independent Non-Executive Director   Pendragon Plc, Mothercare Plc, National Accident Helpline Ltd., Coull Ltd., NAHL Group Plc, Skadoosh Ltd., Ascential Plc, No Agent Technologies Ltd.       expand    All Executives     Robert Stephen Halbert Chairman     John Russell Atkinson Chief Executive Officer & Director     Stephen Dolton Chief Financial Officer & Director     Anthony McGuinness Group Head-Information Technology     Tim Aspinall Non-Executive Director     Marcus Lamont Group Director-Human Resources     Gillian Dawn Celia Kent Independent Non-Executive Director      expand         Advertisement            Average Growth Rates NAHL Group PLC   Past Five Years Ending 12/31/2016 (Fiscal Year)     Revenue  -0.54%    Net Income  +1.73%    Earnings Per Share  +3.95%      Capital Spending  +18.94%    Gross Margin  +51.71%    Cash Flow  -9.17%             Insider Trading NAHL Group PLC   Transaction SummaryTotal Insider Purchases and Sales Reported to the SEC Data not available.   Data not available.           Ownership NAHL Group PLC    Mutual Funds that own NAH     Name Shares Held % Shares Out Change In Shares % of Assets As of Date         St. James's Place Unit Trust - Allshare Income 3,750,000 8.24% 0 0.45% 09/30/16   Schroder Institutional UK Smaller Companies Fund 3,024,980 6.65% +3,024,980 0.56% 11/30/16   Schroder UTL - UK Smaller Companies Fd. 2,903,422 6.38% +1,778,422